====Etymology====
Derived from Latin '''dilapidare''', literally meaning "to destroy with stones", from '''[[dis]]''' (intensive) + '''lapidare''', "to stone" from '''lapis''', "stone"

====Meaning====
# to fall into [[ruin]] or [[disuse]]
# ''(figurative)'' to squander or waste

[[it:dilapidate]]